grants arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe grants undergraduate advising and research grants the office of undergraduate advising and research uar sponsors several types of grants designed to support rigorous independent undergraduate research and creative work in all disciplines including the arts grantee projects should be affiliated with coursework degrees and or honors thesis work for independent extracurricular projects please consider applying for a student arts grant grant types include small grants $1500 limit angel grants $3000 limit major grants $5200 limit chappell lougee scholarships $5200 limit sophomores only conference grants $1500 limit for presentation of work at professional or scholarly conference grants received from the uar can be for any medium such as musical composition painting dance production and written fiction no matter what the medium uar grant proposals must situate projects in a larger creative context they must also offer very specific details about the objectives process and product resulting from the project and show the project's impact on your academic development learn more and apply oil painting by sasha engelmann class of 2011 back home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
